<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-01BF4238-9FC6-42AD-9699-C2D7CC10E2A6" version="2" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-01BF4238-9FC6-42AD-9699-C2D7CC10E2A6" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">SAM : Service Access Management</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M127517-B76"><p class="- topic/p ">To secure access to SDS and TSM on our products we use Service Access Management (SAM).
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Using SAM we can control access to SDS and TSM for each technician and for each product.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The access codes to SDS and TSM are stored on a SAM key. Each technician needs a SAM key to be able to service the product.
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M127517-B74" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">What is needed for SAM?</title><p class="- topic/p ">You need: 
</p><ul id="UL_212B64B66E3C4EC897C8ED9E6B02CB19" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_C01F18A89CEB467F8E1886857E36D6DB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The CodeMeter CmStick (also called CodeMeter dongle or SAM key) 
</p></li><li id="LI_46699859FF314D889F914E6E6B9D0214" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">WIBU CodeMeter Control Center 
</p></li><li id="LI_8908091D4CAA474681B7EEF23E4C7C2B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A license for the products TSM and SDS. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">When have the SAM key, you need to get the required license(s) for TSM and SDS for this product. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Your local ILMS administrator will generate this license and you will get it via email. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This license needs to be stored on the dongle with WIBU CodeMeter Control Center. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This application is part of the CodeMeter runtime kit, which you need to install on your laptop. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The kit is available on the first CD-ROM of WFPS System Tools 1.7 and later triple CD-ROM. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can also download this kit from the “Support &amp; Downloads” section of the Wibu-Systems website 
<xref href="http://www.wibu.com" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>http://www.wibu.com</xref>. 
</p></section><section id="M127517-B77" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Initial steps/first time use.</title><p class="- topic/p ">As a first time user, you need to execute the following steps: 
</p><ul id="UL_9353B1944088411DBCC46080BEB26535" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_4ABDC5FE1DAD4F878D5265875F5267A5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Get a CodeMeter dongle (or SAM key) (from your Support department) 
</p></li><li id="LI_E0BD3A62058C478D9BE5C3BE5B6A5205" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If you didn’t get a mail with the license, you need to get a license for TSM and SDS. (you need to contact the local ILMS administrator and you will get a mail with the license attached). 
</p></li><li id="LI_4F84583B402449C0994C072770B4610C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Download WIBU CodeMeter Runtime kit and install it on the service laptop (run the executable and follow the instructions on the screen). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You can download this kit from the “Support &amp; Downloads” section of the Wibu-Systems website 
<xref href="http://www.wibu.com" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>http://www.wibu.com</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_4EEE3CF61CC2453FBCF670ACB51BB2DA" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Activate the license with CodeMeter Control Center: execute the License Update procedure (see last chapter). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref id="X059686" keyref="SAMINST01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DA30E3F0-AAA7-424A-90DB-5CF29DCD9B20.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text SAM : The 'License Update' Procedure?>SAM : The 'License Update' Procedure</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="M127517-B79" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How does it work?</title><ul id="UL_881AFDE33B3E46638A5501AD68F93112" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_13C50576B5EF4AEBB9BEA47744D9096C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Plug the CodeMeter dongle (or SAM key) in the User Interface Panel. 
</p></li><li id="LI_33C725642BE94B9698581DA165264B13" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Start <ph varid="Adam" translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">ADAM</ph> to use TSM and / or SDS. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="Start_adam" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-685E6504-D43E-4063-96D4-B0A4F752A1F6.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to start ADAM?>How to start ADAM</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="M127517-B90" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">All related documents</title><table id="M127517-TB94" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="1" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="100*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref id="X059688" keyref="SAMINST03" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-40723C59-CBF5-4660-AE67-C0E80D785FB0.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text SAM : The 'Create License Request' procedure?>SAM : The 'Create License Request' procedure</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="SAMINST01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DA30E3F0-AAA7-424A-90DB-5CF29DCD9B20.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text SAM : The 'License Update' Procedure?>SAM : The 'License Update' Procedure</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref id="X059687" keyref="SAMINST02" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-4B086268-3AA3-43BA-AAB7-B73ECEDC28FA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text SAM : The 'Synchronize certified time' procedure?>SAM : The 'Synchronize certified time' procedure</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="SAMDIAG01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-331D6E3F-82C3-417D-AD50-762428C58111.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text SAM : What if SAM does not work?>SAM : What if SAM does not work</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B8949918-A598-4816-BDAF-C06A30443D3A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SAM: Service Access Management</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
